ace Mediation and Constitution Making: The Case for Stronger Interaction and Collaboration -- tRethinking the Professionalization of Peace Mediation -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aWritten by international practitioners and scholars, this pioneering work offers important insights into peace mediation practice today and the role of third parties in the resolution of armed conflicts. The authors reveal how peace mediation has developed into a complex arena and how multifaceted assistance has become an indispensable part of it. Offering unique reflections on the new frameworks set out by the UN, they look at the challenges and opportunities of third-party involvement. With its policy focus and real-world examples from across the globe, this is essential reading for researchers of peace and conflict studies, and a go-to reference point for advisors involved in peace processes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aMediation, International. 0aPeace. 0aReconciliation. 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh1 aFederer, Julia Palmiano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFellin, Irene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroof, Emmanuel De, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirblinger, Andreas T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolper, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKastner, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaye, Josie Lianna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirchhoff, Lars, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlauke, Julian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g